# Turso DB Environment Variables Generator

This script generates a new database in [Turso](https://turso.tech/), the cutting-edge [SQLite](https://www.sqlite.org/)-based cloud database provider. [Turso](https://docs.turso.tech/) offers up to 500 free databases, eliminating the manual hassle of database credential management.

## TLDR:
- Generates a new [Turso](https://turso.tech/product) database
- Runs the [Turso CLI](https://docs.turso.tech/cli/overview) to show database details and copy URL
- Generates a new auth token and copies to clipboard 
- Resulting in the following clipboard:

```bash
DB_URL=libsql://...tursodb.io AUTH_TOKEN=xxxx 
```

- With `--overwrite` flag, overwrites `.env` file and renames old credentials

## Usage

Run the script:

```bash
python *PATH/TO*turso-db-manager.py [--overwrite PATH] 
```
Where `*PATH/TO*` obviously is the path where the script lives, and `[--overwirte PATH]` is the `.env` Which would result in this if you have the sript located in `src/scripts`:
```bash
python3 src/scripts/turso-db-manager.py --overwrite .env
```
<small>--overwrite is optional</small>

### Generate environment variables without saving:

```bash
python generate_tursodb_and_all_enviormentsvars.py 
```

## Environment Variables

- `DB_URL`: Created Turso database URL
- `AUTH_TOKEN`: Database authentication token
<small>If you want different names for the name of the enviorment variable simply search for that string in the source code and replace.</small>

## Requirements

- [Python 3.x](https://www.python.org/)
- [Turso CLI](https://docs.turso.tech/cli/installation)
- `pyperclip` library

## Installation

Install Python library:

```bash
pip install pyperclip 
```

Authenticate with Turso CLI:

```bash
turso auth login 
```

Run the script:

```bash
python3 src/core/scripts/generate_tursodb_and_all_enviormentsvars.py 
```

Example output:

